The paper deals with the problem of compressed sensing, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The focus is on adaptive compressed sensing, which involves choosing measurements based on previous outcomes, making it relevant to the subfield of data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the number of measurements required, which is a topic in numerical analysis (cs.NA), and provides algorithms for implementation, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM).
